✨Air-fried Zinger Burger✨

A delicious homemade Zinger burger that is loaded with crispy chicken/ protein of your choice, lettuce, caramelised onions and mayonnaise *add whatever other ingredients you think* made to perfection at home with @lifelong air frier !

I’ve been loving experimenting with cooking in an air frier from garlic bread, molten cakes to burgers! A true gourmet experience with minimal oil (which means extra healthy)

Recipe:

Air Fried Chicken:

1. Take 4-5 chicken breast and pound them slightly. Cut them into halves. 
2. In a bowl, take 2 cups milk and add 2 tsp vinegar. Stir and keep it aside for 10 minutes. Now add the chicken pieces to it along with salt and pepper to taste. Cover and keep it aside for atleast a couple of hours.
3. Meanwhile in a pan on medium heat, spread 1.5-2 cups panko breadcrumbs. Continue to sauté until light golden. 
4. Transfer toasted breadcrumbs into bowl, add 1 tbsp mixed herbs and salt and pepper to taste.
5. In a bowl, mix 1 egg, 1 tbsp flour, 1 tsp mustard paste, 2 tsp paprika, 1 tsp lemon juice, 1 tsp garlic powder and salt and pepper to taste. Mix it all.
6. Place the chicken pieces in the batter, gently mix to coat. 
7. Pick up chicken pieces, place in breadcrumbs. Spoon over crumb, use fingers to press. Make sure to coat it completely.
8. Transfer to a preheated baking tray/air fryer. Spray with oil(optional) and bake 10-15 minutes or until crispy on the outside.

Try this out and you’re gonna make it your Friday night staple!
PS. it can be made with the protein of your choice - paneer, tofu, or anything!

✨Pita Chips with @modernfoodsin ✨

This Valentine's day, we are showing love to the often ignored last slice of bread because love is for everyone. Enjoy this delicious Pita Chips recipe cooked using the last loaf of bread. 

Let's #TurnHateToLoaf, Happy Valentine's Day. 

Our go to recipe to make crispy homemade chips - the best snack to serve with your favorite dips and salsas! 

Recipe:

1. Take the last slices of bread & cut them into equal triangles. 

2. Transfer it to a tray lined with parchement paper & drizzle some oil, salt, za’atar powder & paprika powder. 

3. Bake it in a preheated oven for 6-8 mins @180*c or until crispy. 

Happy munching !

✨High Protein Rajma Tikki Chaat✨

Chatpata snacking without the post-snack guilt? Yes please! 🤓

Made this rajma tikki chaat using simple, nourishing ingredients, ghee, makhana, cashews, and lots of flavour.
Healthy, hearty & hits all the right notes 🔥🤤😋

Recipe:

-1/2 cup cashews
-1/2 cup makhana 
-1 tsp ghee
-1 tsp grated ginger
-1 cup onion, chopped 
-2 green chillies, chopped
-2 cups rajma, boiled 
-1 tsp amchur powder 
-1 tsp cumin powder
-1 tsp red chilli powder
-1 tsp garam masala 
-Salt to taste
-1 cup cashew makhana powder

To assemble:
-Dahi
-Green chutney 
-Khatti meethi chutney
-Sev
-Pickled beetroot 
-Tikkis

✨Smashed Mexican Tacos✨

Presenting to you, the desi taco of your dreams🤪🌮

Made with a masaledar paneer + rajma filling, a creamy corn & lettuce salad and a serious drizzle of sriracha all wrapped in crispy rotis and smashed till golden.

It’s spicy. It’s tangy. It’s got crunch in every bite, soo
Save it. Make it. Smash it🤓🌮

Recipe:

For the filling:

-200g paneer
-1/2 cup boiled rajma
-2 tsp fried garlic
-1 tsp coriander, chopped
-1 tsp red chilli powder
-1 tsp jeera powder
-Salt to taste

For the salad:

-1 tsp garlic
-1 cup boiled corn
-Salt to taste
-1 cup iceberg lettuce 
-1 cup hung curd
-1 tsp coriander, chopped
-1 tsp chilli flakes
-1 tsp jalapenos, chopped

To assemble:
-1 tsp oil
-Rotis
-Filling

✨High Protein Broccoli Pasta✨

We’ve all tried the classics pesto, Alfredo, arrabbiata, pink sauce...
But have you ever thought of making pasta with broccoli?

When blended into a creamy sauce, broccoli turns into something truly comforting mild, earthy and packed with goodness😮‍💨

It’s one of those feel-good meals that’s light yet satisfying and a clever way to sneak in your greens without even trying🥦🍝

Trust me, this isn’t just “healthy food” it’s comfort in a bowl💛

Recipe:

For the sauce:

-1 head broccoli, blanched
-1 tsp oil
-2 tsp garlic
-1/2 cup onions, chopped
-2 tsp almonds, sliced
-Salt to taste
-1 tsp italian seasoning 
-1 tsp chilli flakes
-1/2 cup basil
-1 cup paneer

For the pasta:

-1 tsp oil
-1 tsp garlic
-1 cup mushrooms, sliced
-1 cup cherry tomatoes, sliced 
-1 tsp red chilli flakes
-1.5 cups broccoli sauce
-1 cup pasta, boiled 
-Black olives & fresh basil to garnish

#BroccoliPasta #weeknightdinner #comfortfood #hiddenveggies #eatyourgreens #PastaIdeas
